{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I want you to put off your preconceptions,"},{"time":3000,"text":"your preconceived fears and thoughts about reptiles."},{"time":8000,"text":"Because that is the only way I'm going to get my story across to you."},{"time":11000,"text":"And by the way, if I come across as a sort of"},{"time":14000,"text":"rabid, hippie conservationist,"},{"time":16000,"text":"it's purely a figment of your imagination."},{"time":19000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":24000,"text":"Okay. We are actually the first species on Earth"},{"time":27000,"text":"to be so prolific to actually threaten our own survival."},{"time":32000,"text":"And I know we've all seen images enough to make us numb,"},{"time":35000,"text":"of the tragedies that we're perpetrating on the planet."},{"time":40000,"text":"We're kind of like greedy kids, using it all up, aren't we?"},{"time":42000,"text":"And today is a time for me to talk to you about water."},{"time":48000,"text":"It's not only because we like to drink lots of it,"},{"time":51000,"text":"and its marvelous derivatives, beer, wine, etc."},{"time":56000,"text":"And, of course, watch it fall from the sky"},{"time":58000,"text":"and flow in our wonderful rivers,"},{"time":61000,"text":"but for several other reasons as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63000,"text":"When I was a kid, growing up in New York,"},{"time":65000,"text":"I was smitten by snakes, the same way most kids are"},{"time":67000,"text":"smitten by tops, marbles, cars, trains, cricket balls."},{"time":72000,"text":"And my mother, brave lady,"},{"time":74000,"text":"was partly to blame,"},{"time":76000,"text":"taking me to the New York Natural History Museum,"},{"time":78000,"text":"buying me books on snakes,"},{"time":80000,"text":"and then starting this infamous career of mine,"},{"time":84000,"text":"which has culminated in"},{"time":86000,"text":"of course, arriving in India 60 years ago,"},{"time":90000,"text":"brought by my mother, Doris Norden,"},{"time":92000,"text":"and my stepfather, Rama Chattopadhyaya."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94000,"text":"It's been a roller coaster ride."},{"time":98000,"text":"Two animals, two iconic reptiles"},{"time":100000,"text":"really captivated me very early on."},{"time":103000,"text":"One of them was the remarkable gharial."},{"time":106000,"text":"This crocodile, which grows to almost 20 feet long"},{"time":108000,"text":"in the northern rivers,"},{"time":110000,"text":"and this charismatic snake, the king cobra."},{"time":115000,"text":"What my purpose of the talk today really is,"},{"time":117000,"text":"is to sort of indelibly scar your minds"},{"time":120000,"text":"with these charismatic and majestic creatures."},{"time":123000,"text":"Because this is what you will take away from here,"},{"time":126000,"text":"a reconnection with nature, I hope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131000,"text":"The king cobra is quite remarkable for several reasons."},{"time":134000,"text":"What you're seeing here is very recently shot images"},{"time":137000,"text":"in a forest nearby here,"},{"time":139000,"text":"of a female king cobra making her nest."},{"time":141000,"text":"Here is a limbless animal, capable of gathering a huge mound of leaves,"},{"time":145000,"text":"and then laying her eggs inside,"},{"time":147000,"text":"to withstand 5 to 10 [meters of rainfall],"},{"time":151000,"text":"in order that the eggs can incubate over the next 90 days,"},{"time":154000,"text":"and hatch into little baby king cobras."},{"time":156000,"text":"So, she protects her eggs,"},{"time":158000,"text":"and after three months,"},{"time":161000,"text":"the babies finally do hatch out."},{"time":163000,"text":"A majority of them will die, of course. There is very high mortality"},{"time":166000,"text":"in little baby reptiles who are just 10 to 12 inches long."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171000,"text":"My first experience with king cobras was in '72"},{"time":173000,"text":"at a magical place called Agumbe,"},{"time":176000,"text":"in Karnataka, this state."},{"time":179000,"text":"And it is a marvelous rain forest."},{"time":182000,"text":"This first encounter"},{"time":184000,"text":"was kind of like the"},{"time":186000,"text":"Maasai boy who kills the lion to become a warrior."},{"time":190000,"text":"It really changed my life totally."},{"time":192000,"text":"And it brought me straight into the conservation fray."},{"time":195000,"text":"I ended up starting this research"},{"time":197000,"text":"and education station in Agumbe,"},{"time":199000,"text":"which you are all of course invited to visit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":202000,"text":"This is basically a base wherein"},{"time":204000,"text":"we are trying to gather and learn"},{"time":206000,"text":"virtually everything about the biodiversity"},{"time":208000,"text":"of this incredibly complex forest system,"},{"time":211000,"text":"and try to hang on to what's there,"},{"time":213000,"text":"make sure the water sources are protected and kept clean,"},{"time":216000,"text":"and of course, having a good time too."},{"time":219000,"text":"You can almost hear the drums"},{"time":221000,"text":"throbbing back in that little cottage where we stay when we're there."},{"time":226000,"text":"It was very important for us to get through to the people."},{"time":230000,"text":"And through the children is usually the way to go."},{"time":233000,"text":"They are fascinated with snakes. They haven't got"},{"time":235000,"text":"that steely thing that you end up"},{"time":238000,"text":"either fearing or hating or despising or loathing them in some way."},{"time":242000,"text":"They are interested."},{"time":244000,"text":"And it really works to start with them."},{"time":246000,"text":"This gives you an idea of the size of some of these snakes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248000,"text":"This is an average size king cobra, about 12 feet long."},{"time":251000,"text":"And it actually crawled into somebody's bathroom,"},{"time":253000,"text":"and was hanging around there for two or three days."},{"time":255000,"text":"The people of this part of India"},{"time":257000,"text":"worship the king cobra."},{"time":259000,"text":"And they didn't kill it. They called us to catch it."},{"time":261000,"text":"Now we've caught more than 100 king cobras"},{"time":263000,"text":"over the last three years,"},{"time":265000,"text":"and relocated them in nearby forests."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268000,"text":"But in order to find out the real secrets of these creatures"},{"time":271000,"text":"[it was necessary] for us to actually insert"},{"time":274000,"text":"a small radio transmitter inside [each] snake."},{"time":277000,"text":"Now we are able to follow them and find out their secrets,"},{"time":281000,"text":"where the babies go after they hatch,"},{"time":284000,"text":"and remarkable things like this you're about to see."},{"time":288000,"text":"This was just a few days ago in Agumbe."},{"time":290000,"text":"I had the pleasure of being close to this large king cobra"},{"time":295000,"text":"who had caught a venomous pit viper."},{"time":297000,"text":"And it does it in such a way that it doesn't get bitten itself."},{"time":300000,"text":"And king cobras feed only on snakes."},{"time":304000,"text":"This [little snake] was kind of a tid-bit for it,"},{"time":306000,"text":"what we'd call a \"vadai\" or a donut or something like that."},{"time":308000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":311000,"text":"Usually they eat something a bit larger."},{"time":313000,"text":"In this case a rather strange and inexplicable"},{"time":317000,"text":"activity happened over the last breeding season,"},{"time":320000,"text":"wherein a large male king cobra actually grabbed a female king cobra,"},{"time":324000,"text":"didn't mate with it, actually killed it and swallowed it."},{"time":327000,"text":"We're still trying to explain and come to terms with"},{"time":329000,"text":"what is the evolutionary advantage of this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334000,"text":"But they do also a lot of other remarkable things."},{"time":337000,"text":"This is again, something [we were able to see] by virtue of the fact"},{"time":339000,"text":"that we had a radio transmitter in one of the snakes."},{"time":342000,"text":"This male snake, 12 feet long, met another male king cobra."},{"time":345000,"text":"And they did this incredible ritual combat dance."},{"time":349000,"text":"It's very much like the rutting of mammals, including humans,"},{"time":351000,"text":"you know, sorting out our differences, but gentler, no biting allowed."},{"time":355000,"text":"It's just a wresting match,"},{"time":357000,"text":"but a remarkable activity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":359000,"text":"Now, what are we doing with all this information?"},{"time":361000,"text":"What's the point of all this?"},{"time":363000,"text":"Well, the king cobra is literally"},{"time":365000,"text":"a keystone species in these rainforests."},{"time":368000,"text":"And our job is to convince the authorities"},{"time":372000,"text":"that these forests have to be protected."},{"time":374000,"text":"And this is one of the ways we do it,"},{"time":376000,"text":"by learning as much as we can"},{"time":378000,"text":"about something so remarkable and so iconic in the rainforests there,"},{"time":382000,"text":"in order to help protect trees, animals"},{"time":385000,"text":"and of course the water sources."}]},{"cues":[{"time":387000,"text":"You've all heard, perhaps, of Project Tiger"},{"time":389000,"text":"which started back in the early '70s,"},{"time":392000,"text":"which was, in fact, a very dynamic time for conservation."},{"time":396000,"text":"We were piloted, I could say,"},{"time":399000,"text":"by a highly autocratic stateswoman,"},{"time":401000,"text":"but who also had an incredible passion for environment."},{"time":405000,"text":"And this is the time when Project Tiger emerged."},{"time":408000,"text":"And, just like Project Tiger,"},{"time":411000,"text":"our activities with the king cobra"},{"time":413000,"text":"is to look at a species of animal"},{"time":415000,"text":"so that we protect its habitat and everything within it."},{"time":418000,"text":"So, the tiger is the icon."},{"time":420000,"text":"And now the king cobra is a new one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424000,"text":"All the major rivers in south India"},{"time":426000,"text":"are sourced in the Western Ghats,"},{"time":428000,"text":"the chain of hills running along the west coast of India."},{"time":432000,"text":"It pours out millions of gallons every hour,"},{"time":435000,"text":"and supplies drinking water to at least 300 million people,"},{"time":439000,"text":"and washes many, many babies,"},{"time":442000,"text":"and of course feeds many, many animals,"},{"time":445000,"text":"both domestic and wild,"},{"time":447000,"text":"produces thousands of tons of rice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449000,"text":"And what do we do? How do we respond to this?"},{"time":451000,"text":"Well, basically, we dam it, we pollute it,"},{"time":453000,"text":"we pour in pesticides, weedicides, fungicides."},{"time":456000,"text":"You drink it in peril of your life."},{"time":459000,"text":"And the thing is, it's not just big industry."},{"time":462000,"text":"It's not misguided river engineers"},{"time":464000,"text":"who are doing all this; it's us."},{"time":466000,"text":"It seems that our citizens find the best way to dispose of garbage"},{"time":470000,"text":"are in water sources."},{"time":472000,"text":"Okay. Now we're going north, very far north."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475000,"text":"North central India, the Chambal River"},{"time":477000,"text":"is where we have our base."},{"time":479000,"text":"This is the home of the gharial, this incredible crocodile."},{"time":483000,"text":"It is an animal which has been on the Earth"},{"time":486000,"text":"for just about 100 million years."},{"time":489000,"text":"It survived even during the time that the dinosaurs died off."},{"time":493000,"text":"It has remarkable features."},{"time":495000,"text":"Even though it grows to 20 feet long,"},{"time":497000,"text":"since it eats only fish it's not dangerous to human beings."},{"time":500000,"text":"It does have big teeth, however,"},{"time":502000,"text":"and it's kind of hard to convince people"},{"time":504000,"text":"if an animal has big teeth, that it's a harmless creature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":507000,"text":"But we, actually, back in the early '70s,"},{"time":511000,"text":"did surveys,"},{"time":513000,"text":"and found that gharial were extremely rare."},{"time":517000,"text":"In fact, if you see the map,"},{"time":519000,"text":"the range of their original habitat"},{"time":521000,"text":"was all the way from the Indus in Pakistan"},{"time":524000,"text":"to the Irrawaddy in Burma."},{"time":526000,"text":"And now it's just limited to a couple of spots"},{"time":528000,"text":"in Nepal and India."},{"time":530000,"text":"So, in fact at this point"},{"time":533000,"text":"there are only 200 breeding gharial left in the wild."},{"time":537000,"text":"So, starting in the mid-'70s"},{"time":539000,"text":"when conservation was at the fore,"},{"time":542000,"text":"we were actually able to start projects which were"},{"time":545000,"text":"basically government supported"},{"time":547000,"text":"to collect eggs from the wild from the few remaining nests"},{"time":550000,"text":"and release 5,000 baby gharial"},{"time":552000,"text":"back to the wild."},{"time":554000,"text":"And pretty soon we were seeing sights like this."},{"time":557000,"text":"I mean, just incredible to see bunches of gharial"},{"time":560000,"text":"basking on the river again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":562000,"text":"But complacency does have a tendency to breed contempt."},{"time":566000,"text":"And, sure enough, with all the other pressures on the river,"},{"time":569000,"text":"like sand mining, for example,"},{"time":572000,"text":"very, very heavy cultivation all the way down to the river's edge,"},{"time":576000,"text":"not allowing the animals to breed anymore,"},{"time":578000,"text":"we're looking at"},{"time":581000,"text":"even more problems building up for the gharial,"},{"time":584000,"text":"despite the early good intentions."},{"time":586000,"text":"Their nests hatching along the riverside"},{"time":590000,"text":"producing hundreds of hatchlings. It's just an amazing sight."},{"time":593000,"text":"This was actually just taken last year."},{"time":595000,"text":"But then the monsoon arrives,"},{"time":599000,"text":"and unfortunately downriver there is always a dam or"},{"time":601000,"text":"there is always a barrage,"},{"time":603000,"text":"and, shoop, they get washed down to their doom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":607000,"text":"Luckily there is still a lot of interest."},{"time":609000,"text":"My pals in the Crocodile Specialist Group of the IUCN,"},{"time":612000,"text":"the [Madras Crocodile Bank], an NGO,"},{"time":614000,"text":"the World Wildlife Fund,"},{"time":616000,"text":"the Wildlife Institute of India, State Forest Departments,"},{"time":619000,"text":"and the Ministry of Environment, we all work together on stuff."},{"time":622000,"text":"But it's possibly, and definitely not enough."},{"time":626000,"text":"For example, in the winter of 2007 and 2008,"},{"time":631000,"text":"there was this incredible die-off of gharial, in the Chambal River."},{"time":635000,"text":"Suddenly dozens of gharial appearing on the river, dead."},{"time":637000,"text":"Why? How could it happen?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":639000,"text":"This is a relatively clean river."},{"time":641000,"text":"The Chambal, if you look at it, has clear water."},{"time":644000,"text":"People scoop water out of the Chambal and drink it,"},{"time":646000,"text":"something you wouldn't do in most north Indian rivers."},{"time":649000,"text":"So, in order to try to find out the answer to this,"},{"time":652000,"text":"we got veterinarians from all over the world"},{"time":654000,"text":"working with Indian vets to try to figure out what was happening."},{"time":657000,"text":"I was there for a lot of the necropsies on the riverside."},{"time":661000,"text":"And we actually looked through"},{"time":663000,"text":"all their organs and tried to figure out what was going on."},{"time":666000,"text":"And it came down to something called gout,"},{"time":669000,"text":"which, as a result of kidney breakdown"},{"time":672000,"text":"is actually uric acid crystals throughout the body,"},{"time":675000,"text":"and worse in the joints,"},{"time":678000,"text":"which made the gharial unable to swim."},{"time":681000,"text":"And it's a horribly painful death."}]},{"cues":[{"time":683000,"text":"Just downriver from the Chambal is the"},{"time":685000,"text":"filthy Yamuna river, the sacred Yamuna river."},{"time":688000,"text":"And I hate to be so ironic and sarcastic about it"},{"time":692000,"text":"but it's the truth. It's just one of the filthiest cesspools you can imagine."},{"time":695000,"text":"It flows down through Delhi, Mathura, Agra,"},{"time":699000,"text":"and gets just about every bit of effluent you can imagine."},{"time":702000,"text":"So, it seemed that the toxin that was killing the gharial"},{"time":706000,"text":"was something in the food chain,"},{"time":708000,"text":"something in the fish they were eating."},{"time":710000,"text":"And, you know, once a toxin is in the food chain"},{"time":712000,"text":"everything is affected, including us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":715000,"text":"Because these rivers are the lifeblood of people all along their course."},{"time":719000,"text":"In order to try to answer some of these questions,"},{"time":721000,"text":"we again turn to technology,"},{"time":723000,"text":"to biological technology, in this case,"},{"time":726000,"text":"again, telemetry, putting radios on 10 gharial,"},{"time":730000,"text":"and actually following their movements. They're being watched"},{"time":732000,"text":"everyday as we speak, to try to find out"},{"time":734000,"text":"what this mysterious toxin is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":737000,"text":"The Chambal river is an absolutely incredible place."},{"time":741000,"text":"It's a place that's famous to a lot of you who know"},{"time":744000,"text":"about the bandits, the dacoits"},{"time":747000,"text":"who used to work up there. And there still are quite a few around."},{"time":750000,"text":"But Poolan Devi was one [of them]. Which actually Shekhar Kapur"},{"time":753000,"text":"made an incredible movie, \"The Bandit Queen,\" which I urge you to see."},{"time":756000,"text":"You'll get to see the incredible [Chambal] landscape as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":759000,"text":"But, again, heavy fishing pressures."},{"time":763000,"text":"This is one of the last repositories of the"},{"time":766000,"text":"Ganges river dolphin,"},{"time":768000,"text":"various species of turtles,"},{"time":770000,"text":"thousands of migratory birds,"},{"time":772000,"text":"and fishing is causing problems like this."},{"time":775000,"text":"And now [these] new elements of human intolerance"},{"time":780000,"text":"for river creatures like the gharial"},{"time":783000,"text":"means that if they don't drown in the net,"},{"time":786000,"text":"then they simply cut their beaks off."},{"time":788000,"text":"Animals like the Ganges river dolphin"},{"time":790000,"text":"which is just down to a few left,"},{"time":792000,"text":"and it is also critically endangered."}]},{"cues":[{"time":794000,"text":"So, who is next? Us?"},{"time":796000,"text":"Because we are all dependent on these water sources."},{"time":799000,"text":"So, we all know about the Narmada river,"},{"time":801000,"text":"the tragedies of dams, the tragedies of huge projects"},{"time":804000,"text":"which displace people and wreck river systems"},{"time":807000,"text":"without providing livelihoods."},{"time":809000,"text":"And development just basically going berserk,"},{"time":812000,"text":"for a double figure growth index, basically."},{"time":815000,"text":"So, we're not sure where this story is going to end,"},{"time":820000,"text":"whether it's got a happy or sad ending."},{"time":822000,"text":"And climate change is certainly going"},{"time":824000,"text":"to turn all of our theories and predictions on their heads."},{"time":827000,"text":"We're still working hard at it."},{"time":829000,"text":"We've got a lot of a good team of people working up there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":832000,"text":"And the thing is, you know, the decision makers,"},{"time":835000,"text":"the folks in power,"},{"time":837000,"text":"they're up in their bungalows and so on in Delhi,"},{"time":839000,"text":"in the city capitals. They are all supplied with plenty of water. It's cool."},{"time":842000,"text":"But out on the rivers there are still millions of people"},{"time":845000,"text":"who are in really bad shape."},{"time":848000,"text":"And it's a bleak future for them."},{"time":850000,"text":"So, we have our Ganges and Yamuna cleanup project."},{"time":853000,"text":"We've spent hundreds of millions of dollars on it,"},{"time":855000,"text":"and nothing to show for it. Incredible."},{"time":858000,"text":"So, people talk about political will."},{"time":861000,"text":"During the die-off of the gharial we did galvanize a lot of action."},{"time":864000,"text":"Government cut through all the red tape,"},{"time":866000,"text":"we got foreign vets on it. It was great."},{"time":868000,"text":"So, we can do it."},{"time":870000,"text":"But if you stroll down to the Yamuna"},{"time":872000,"text":"or to the Gomati in Lucknow,"},{"time":874000,"text":"or to the Adyar river in Chennai,"},{"time":877000,"text":"or the Mula-Mutha river in Pune,"},{"time":880000,"text":"just see what we're capable of doing to a river. It's sad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":884000,"text":"But I think the final note really is"},{"time":887000,"text":"that we can do it."},{"time":890000,"text":"The corporates, the artists, the wildlife nuts,"},{"time":893000,"text":"the good old everyday folks"},{"time":895000,"text":"can actually bring these rivers back."},{"time":898000,"text":"And the final word is"},{"time":900000,"text":"that there is a king cobra looking over our shoulders."},{"time":904000,"text":"And there is a gharial looking at us from the river."},{"time":907000,"text":"And these are powerful water totems."},{"time":909000,"text":"And they are going to disturb our dreams until we do the right thing."},{"time":913000,"text":"Namaste."},{"time":915000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":921000,"text":"Chris Anderson: Thanks, Rom. Thanks a lot."},{"time":924000,"text":"You know, most people are terrified of snakes."},{"time":927000,"text":"And there might be quite a few people here who would be"},{"time":929000,"text":"very glad to see the last king cobra bite the dust."},{"time":932000,"text":"Do you have those conversations with people?"},{"time":935000,"text":"How do you really get them to care?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":937000,"text":"Romulus Whitaker: I take the sort of humble approach,"},{"time":942000,"text":"I guess you could say. I don't say that snakes are huggable exactly."},{"time":946000,"text":"It's not like the teddy bear."},{"time":949000,"text":"But I sort of -- there is an innocence in these animals."},{"time":953000,"text":"And when the average person looks at a cobra"},{"time":955000,"text":"going \"Ssssss!\" like that, they say, \"My god,"},{"time":957000,"text":"look at that angry, dangerous creature.\""},{"time":959000,"text":"I look at it as a creature who is totally frightened"},{"time":962000,"text":"of something so dangerous as a human being."},{"time":965000,"text":"And that is the truth. And that's what I try to get out."},{"time":968000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":972000,"text":"CA: Now, incredible footage you showed of the viper being killed."},{"time":974000,"text":"You were saying that that hasn't been filmed before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":977000,"text":"RW: Yes, this is actually the first time anyone of us knew about it, for one thing."},{"time":980000,"text":"As I said, it's just like a little snack for him, you know?"},{"time":983000,"text":"Usually they eat larger snakes like rat snakes,"},{"time":985000,"text":"or even cobras."},{"time":987000,"text":"But this guy who we're following right now is in the deep jungle."},{"time":990000,"text":"Whereas other king cobras"},{"time":992000,"text":"very often come into the human interface,"},{"time":994000,"text":"you know, the plantations, to find big rat snakes and stuff."},{"time":997000,"text":"This guy specializes in pit vipers."},{"time":1000000,"text":"And the guy who is working there with them,"},{"time":1002000,"text":"he's from Maharashtra, he said, \"I think he's after the nusha.\""},{"time":1005000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1007000,"text":"Now, the nusha means the high."},{"time":1009000,"text":"Whenever he eats the pit viper he gets this little venom rush."},{"time":1012000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1014000,"text":"CA: Thanks Rom. Thank you."},{"time":1016000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}